location.city_name: Silfra Rift, Þingvellir National Park, Iceland

social_posts.post_text: Snorkeling in 36 degree glacier water between the Eurasian and North American tectonic plates! Ice from Langjökull (Iceland’s second largest glacier) melts and seeps into the earth where it’s filtered by porous lava rock for 40-100 years before emerging from this fissure between the two tectonic plates. The water is incredibly clear, drinkable, and very cold. We wore dry suits so we wouldn’t freeze (Lo’s leaked lol) but our lips were so cold they turned purple. Totally worth it though. I’ve never seen or felt anything like this. Nature is magic. #iceland #icelandtravel #snorkeling @laydeelo

Arrived in a super jeep. Hiked on a glacier. Explored an ice cave with layered walls of ancient ice and volcanic ash. Iceland is blowing my mind. @laydeelo @hingaflips #iceland #icelandtravel #icecave #katla #climbing #adventure

3. Afternoon Tea with the ladies 🫖
4. Playing at the park with Floki 🐶

7. Christmas gifts my grandma bought for me and my sister before she passed away. This was our first Christmas without her. She bought presents all year round (for everyone), stashed them away, and then hand wrapped them each year (each of them signed “From: SANTA”). She also bought and wrapped dozens of extra “presents” for her white elephant game. We missed her this year. We played the white elephant game in her honor, though it lacked the customary kitchen utensils and odd figurines lol. We miss you grandma ❤️🕊️

Bird woman 🦅 #dubai 

Falcons are a cultural symbol of the UAE, thanks to their part in their skill and unique personalities. This bird of prey played a vital role in Bedouins’ (nomadic Arab people) lives, with falcons hunting bustard, curlews and other animals for food.

Gold & Spice Souk (market) 🌶️ Hard negotiation tactics with jeweler = bought a beautiful ring for 1/2 the price it would be in the USA. Underestimated the spice man = somehow paid $200 for 4 bags of spices. We had quite an interesting day exploring old Dubai #gold #dubai #traveltips
